        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 8 at 4:19PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 419 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles west of Conlen, or 13 miles north of Dalhart, moving southeast
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Conlen.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
